Some 400 Baringo residents in Nairobi have set up a forum to discuss county issues.Chairman Wilson Kandie yesterday said they have also formed a WhatsApp group to notify members about drought and hunger in the region. During a meeting at a Nairobi hotel, Kandie said Tiaty constituency is the worst hit. He said they have met Deputy President William Ruto and Devolution secretary Simeon ole Kirgotty, who promised to help them ease the situation. The group has 400 members, Kandie said.